835
00:58:36,630 --> 00:58:38,308
Speaker 0: I was laughing my ass off at that.

836
00:58:38,870 --> 00:58:41,989
Speaker 0: And if they just left all the French in, it just wouldn't have been funny at all.

837
00:58:42,912 --> 00:58:48,670
Speaker 0: So mainly, yeah, professional companies, they use formal equivalents and that's what fansubs used to do.

838
00:58:49,130 --> 00:58:52,650
Speaker 0: They used to try and be professional, is the point of my video.

839
00:58:53,230 --> 00:59:02,970
Speaker 2: A lot of earlier anime releases would take the music and re-perform it in English to kind of translate the music along with it.

