Speaker 0: It's totally impossible.

1046
01:13:00,607 --> 01:13:01,410
Speaker 0: You just can't do it.

1047
01:13:01,570 --> 01:13:04,170
Speaker 0: So things have to go a lot of the time, unfortunately.

1048
01:13:04,990 --> 01:13:15,750
Speaker 0: Unless you're working designs, which was another translation company that got a bit of slack because they went too far and would just start putting American pop culture into the translation system.

1049
01:13:15,890 --> 01:13:27,230
Speaker 0: But what they would do was actually, they wouldn't just translate, they'd rewrite the code of the game and allow themselves more space and things like that, which was absolutely insane.

1050
01:13:27,510 --> 01:13:35,310
Speaker 0: I mean, they went beyond the call of duty, but they went under because of it, because it took so long to release each game, was the trouble.

1051
01:13:36,831 --> 01:13:45,030
Speaker 1: Do you think it would help if when they originally made the game, they just put all the different languages in there from the start, the same way they do with DVDs and such?

1052
01:13:46,472 --> 01:13:50,790
