1053
01:13:52,010 --> 01:14:08,230
Speaker 0: Because, I mean, I could be wrong, but the way it seems to work is that, obviously, the Japanese first, and then that gets sent to a translator who does the English one, and then the English one is taken as a basis and all the European languages are done from that.

1054
01:14:08,872 --> 01:14:14,750
Speaker 0: So you can, I mean, it may be different with different companies, but that's been my experience.

1055
01:14:15,250 --> 01:14:20,630
Speaker 0: And so if someone makes a mistake in the English, that mistake's passed down into all the European languages.

1056
01:14:21,552 --> 01:14:26,010
Speaker 0: But yeah, it would take ages to get all the languages in at once.

1057
01:14:26,610 --> 01:14:33,870
