01:16:38,910 --> 01:16:43,830
Speaker 0: So, I'm a complete moron, I'm surprised I get any jobs at all after some of the stuff that I've pulled.

1082
01:16:44,471 --> 01:16:48,050
Speaker 1: So, you work on your own, you don't have an agent or anything?

1083
01:16:48,972 --> 01:16:58,830
Speaker 0: I work for agencies, actually, because I've got my details on translation websites like Prose and Translators Cafe and things like that.

1084
01:16:59,010 --> 01:17:03,209
Speaker 0: So, people see that and they see that I specialize in games and novels and they contact me.

1085
01:17:04,030 --> 01:17:09,530
Speaker 0: And if you get a good working relationship with a company going, then, I mean, that's excellent, really.

1086
01:17:10,070 --> 01:17:22,730
Speaker 0: I mean, there's a company called Local Soft in Spain who are really, really good because they won't just send you the text to translate, they'll send you scans, all the scans you need, all of the glossaries and terminologies.

1087
01:17:23,170 --> 01:17:33,870
Speaker 0: If it's a game for the DS, you know, you'll get a glossary of every single DS part, the names of every component in the DS, so that you can make sure your translation's, like, spot-on perfect.

1088
01:17:33,930 --> 01:17:36,946
Speaker 1: So, you get to see some games, like, before they come out.

1089
01:17:37,046 --> 01:17:37,730
