1093
01:17:47,292 --> 01:17:49,069
Speaker 0: But you're not seeing what's happening on the screen.

1094
01:17:50,011 --> 01:17:58,130
Speaker 0: And so, a lot of bad translations stem from that, from the fact that you can see someone saying something, but you don't know what's actually happening is the trouble.

1095
01:18:00,210 --> 01:18:14,230
Speaker 0: So, I mean, ideally, and people like Jeremy Blaustein and, like, you know, the real big names in translation industry, I'm guessing that they are playing the beta test versions of the games as they translate, and that's what you need to do, really.

1096
01:18:14,731 --> 01:18:22,090
Speaker 0: And I know that my friend Ben, for some companies, they actually send him the game as well, which he plays and translates as he goes along.

1097
01:18:23,010 --> 01:18:27,049
